<table class="contentpaneopen">



<tr>
<td valign="top">
<p>There is no doubt about it; redundancies are stressful. Stressful for all concerned, not least those whose position is at the threat of redundancy, and those in the Organisation having to consider, sanction and undertake the redundancy processes.</p>
<p>When considering redundancies, preparation, transparency and fairness are the key three points. The Organisation needs to be certain, and be able to prove, a diminuation of work which would lead to a redundancy. You need to be able to share this information with the employees at risk of redundancy and also you must then be able to decide fairly and objectively who stays and who goes.</p>
<p>Redundancies can have a profound impact on the Organisation, not least in terms of risk of an employment tribunal case, but also in the less tangible, but equally important, feelings and motivation of your workforce.</p>
<p>Talk to Eden HR; We can talk through with you the fundamentals of the redundancy process, conduct the entire process on your behalf, right the way through to outplacement services and survivor training in order to boost morale after redundancies have taken place</p>
<p> </p></td>
